the8472.utils.concurrent

Class NonblockingScheduledExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • the8472.utils.concurrent.NonblockingScheduledExecutor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Executor, ExecutorService, ScheduledExecutorService

    public class NonblockingScheduledExecutor
extends Object
implements ScheduledExecutorService
    used a linked transfer queue for non-scheduled tasks to achieve high throughput / avoid lock contention. scheduled tasks are handled by a dedicated runnable executed in one of the executor's threads - gets re-circulated through the LTQ - yields its own thread back to the executor when load depands it - only ever that one instance active at a time -> sequential behavior -> we can use a lock-free priority queue - wakeups happen either based on the next scheduled task or cooperatively with executor methods
